        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I mean, there's no point to having `foo.12345.0` and `foo.12345.1` in the same directory belonging to the same process.\r\n\r\nNeither is there much purpose to calling `serverstart(\"foo\")` twice in the same instance (without calling serverstop in-between). So I was wondering what the use was and whether Neovim could drop the `.counter` suffix.\r\n\r\ncalling serverstart a second time while the socket already exists should simply return it's path again, since there's no limit on active connections to a Unix socket as far as I know.",
